### Key Findings

- **Design target**: Card with `bg-surface-container-low rounded-2xl border border-white/5`, avatar (`w-20 h-20 rounded-full ring-2 ring-primary/20`), name (`font-bold text-lg`), subtitle (`text-xs text-on-surface-variant`), and mail/call buttons — all from `design/reli_ai_chat_panel/code.html` lines 185–198.
- **Critical token gap**: The design references `surface-container-highest` for button backgrounds, but that token doesn't exist in `index.css` — use `surface-container-high` instead.
- **Icon strategy**: Project uses inline SVG throughout (no icon library), so mail and phone icons must be inline SVG `<path>` elements matching the existing `stroke="currentColor"` pattern in DetailPanel.
- **Action links**: Use `<a href="mailto:...">` and `<a href="tel:...">` styled as buttons — native browser behavior, mobile-friendly, no JS needed.
- **Data fields**: `email`, `phone`, `role`, `company` come from `thing.data` (a `Record<string, unknown>`); filter them from the generic data entries list when rendering the contact card to avoid duplication.

### Gaps

- `on-primary` color token is not defined in `index.css` — use `text-on-surface` for hover text color on primary button background.
- `picture_url` field for avatar image has no existing usage — the initials fallback is the reliable implementation path.
