---

### Summary

Add a Contact card to `DetailPanel.tsx` that renders for `type_hint === 'person'` Things: initials avatar circle, name, optional role/title, and `mailto:`/`tel:` icon buttons. Email/phone/role come from `thing.data`. Also suppress those fields from the generic Details section to avoid duplication. No new packages needed — uses inline SVG (matching existing SVG at line 108-115), the Reli Suggestion card container style, and the `text-people`/`bg-people` color tokens already defined.

### Metadata

| Field | Value |
|-------|-------|
| Complexity | LOW |
| Files to UPDATE | 3 |
| Files to CREATE | 0 |
| Total Tasks | 4 |

### Key Patterns Discovered

- Reli Suggestion card at `DetailPanel.tsx:263-280` — IIFE + `rounded-xl bg-surface-container-highest/30 border-l-4` — exact style template
- `typeColorClasses()` at `DetailPanel.tsx:28-29` — `'person'` → `text-people` / `bg-people/15`
- `dataEntries` filter at `DetailPanel.tsx:130-132` — extend to exclude contact keys for person type
- Existing screenshot test at `visual.spec.ts:381-398` — click-then-screenshot pattern to follow

### UX Transformation

- **BEFORE**: Person Things render identically to all other types; email/phone buried in raw data fields
- **AFTER**: Dedicated Contact card with initials avatar, role line, and one-tap mail/call buttons at top of content

### Risks

- Primary: `thing.data` field naming varies (`role` vs `title` vs `position`) — mitigated by fallback chain
- Screenshot test timing — mitigated by `waitForSelector('[aria-label="Send Email"]')` gate

### Confidence Score

**9/10** — the feature maps exactly to an existing pattern (Reli Suggestion card), all data is already in the store, no new dependencies, and test infrastructure is already wired. The only uncertainty is field naming variation in real user data, which is handled by the fallback chain.
